<br>
Step 1)  Get hammer.  This raises your OT faction to amiable.<br>
Step 1a) If you really care about OT faction get it higher just in case.<br>
Step 2)  Get 50+.  Yeah, its redundant I know.<br>
Step 3)  Buy all your mage spells off vendor, put em on an alt.<br>
Step 3a) If you have no room for characters on your account, see below.<br>
Step 4)  Kill rottgrime.  With faction hits from several pulls I ended at dubious (non kos) from amiable.<br>
Step 5)  If you care to have OT faction at this point, raise it back up.  The ruins are an easy way to solo for war braids fairly fast and some xp there (few are still xp con).<br>
Step 6)  You now have all your spells and your epic part and your hammer and you are not kos here.  If you did not have room for spells then dont hunt in any bad faction dungeons until you either raise faction or level high enough to get them.  Alternatively have a lower level from zone buy them when you need em.  Or a guildy.  Or use the bazzar.  There are a lot of ways to get around the faction and the spell purchase issues.<br>
Step 7)  If, like me, you dont care about your faction at this point since all you could do is bank/buy/sell, then go nutz in the dungeons.<br>
<br>
That should clear up any issues with the faction.  Simply trying to keep it past the 50s bars you access to so many places its just not worth it, IMO.  Just get the hammer and toss the spells on an alt, then kill for epic part and dont look back.  Seriously, how many times can you not find a bank ....<br>
<br>
And btw, longest it took me to proc it was just over a minute of swinging, typically it goes after a dozen or less.  Thats with dex 85 and 2hb of 25.<br>
